/span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> v</span>} →\n  <span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\">inst</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bind\">Bind</a> <span class=\"fn\">m</span></span>] →\n    <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">instCCPO</span> : <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">β</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u) → <span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nonempty\">Nonempty</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span>] → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Internal/Order/Basic.html#Lean.Order.CCPO\">Lean.Order.CCPO</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">m</span> <span class=\"fn\">β</span>)</span></span></span></span>) →\n      <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(∀ {<span class=\"fn\">α </span><span class=\"fn\">β</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u} {<span class=\"fn\">a</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">m</span> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>} {<span class=\"fn\">f₁ </span><span class=\"fn\">f₂</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">m</span> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span></span>} [<span class=\"fn\">inst_1</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nonempty\">Nonempty</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span>],\n          <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(∀ (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Internal/Order/Basic.html#Lean.Order.PartialOrder.rel\">Lean.Order.PartialOrder.rel</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f₁</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f₂</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span>)</span></span>)</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Internal/Order/Basic.html#Lean.Order.PartialOrder.rel\">Lean.Order.PartialOrder.rel</a> (<span class=\"fn\">a</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bind.bind\">&gt;&gt;=</a> <span class=\"fn\">f₁</span>) (<span class=\"fn\">a</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bind.bind\">&gt;&gt;=</a> <span class=\"fn\">f₂</span>)</span></span>)</span> →\n        <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Internal/Order/MonadTail.html#Lean.Order.MonadTail\">Lean.Order.MonadTail</a> <span class=\"fn\">m</span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Init/Internal/Order/MonadTail.html#Lean.Order.MonadTail.mk","kind":"ctor","line":18,"name":"Lean.Order.MonadTail.mk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Init/Internal/Order/MonadTail.lean#L18-L32"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">class</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Internal/Order/MonadTail.html#Lean.Order.MonadTail\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Order</span>.<span class=\"name\">MonadTail</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">m</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> v</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bind\">Bind</a> <span class=\"fn\">m</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> (max (u + 1) v)</div></div>","info":{"doc":"A *tail monad* is a monad whose bind operation preserves a chosen ordering of the continuation.\nSpecifically, `MonadTail m` asserts that every `m β` carries a chain-complete partial order (CCPO)\nand that `>>=` is monotone in its second (continuation) argument with respect to that order.\n\nThis is a weaker requirement than `MonoBind`, which requires monotonicity in both arguments.\n`MonadTail` is sufficient for `partial_fixpoint`-like recursive definitions where the\nrecursive call only appears in the continuation (second argument) of `>>=`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Internal/Order/MonadTail.html#Lean.Order.MonadTail","kind":"class","line":18,"name":"Lean.Order.MonadTail","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Init/Internal/Order/MonadTail.lean#L18-L32"}}],"imports":["Init.Internal.Order.Basic","Init.System.ST"],"instances":[{"className":"Lean.Order.MonadTail","name":"Lean.Order.instMonadTailId","typeNames":["Id"]},{"className":"Lean.Order.MonadTail","name":"Lean.Order.instMonadTailStateTOfNonempty","typeNames":["StateT"]},{"className":"Lean.Order.MonadTail","name":"Lean.Order.instMonadTailExceptT","typeNames":["ExceptT"]},{"className":"Lean.Order.MonadTail","name":"Lean.Order.instMonadTailExcept","typeNames":["Except"]},{"className":"Lean.Order.MonadTail","name":"Lean.Order.instMonadTailOptionT","typeNames":["OptionT"]},{"className":"Lean.Order.MonadTail","name":"Lean.Order.instMonadTailOption","typeNames":["Option"]},{"className":"Lean.Order.MonadTail","name":"Lean.Order.instMonadTailReaderT","typeNames":["ReaderT"]},{"className":"Lean.Order.CCPO","name":"Lean.Order.instCCPOSTOfNonempty","typeNames":["ST"]},{"className":"Lean.Order.MonadTail","name":"Lean.Order.instMonadTailST","typeNames":["ST"]},{"className":"Lean.Order.MonadTail","name":"Lean.Order.instMonadTailBaseIO","typeNames":["BaseIO"]},{"className":"Lean.Order.MonadTail","name":"Lean.Order.instMonadTailESTOfNonempty","typeNames":["EST"]},{"className":"Lean.Order.MonadTail","name":"Lean.Order.instMonadTailEIOOfNonempty","typeNames":["EIO"]},{"className":"Lean.Order.MonadTail","name":"Lean.Order.instMonadTailIO","typeNames":["IO"]},{"className":"Lean.Order.MonadTail","name":"Lean.Order.instMonadTailStateRefT'","typeNames":["StateRefT'"]}],"name":"Init.Internal.Order.MonadTail"}